### Component 6: Voice Logging

#### In `frontend/src/components/VoiceInput.jsx`
- Uses browser `webkitSpeechRecognition` / `SpeechRecognition` API
- Microphone button with recording pulse animation
- Real-time transcript display
- On stop → sends transcript text to the chat agent (same `/api/chat` endpoint)
- Graceful fallback: if browser doesn't support it, button is hidden

No backend changes needed — voice is converted to text client-side, then processed by the same LangGraph agent.

---

### Component 7: PDF Export

#### In `backend/api/routes.py` — `GET /api/interactions/{id}/pdf`
- Uses `reportlab` or `fpdf2` to generate a clean PDF
- Contents: Interaction summary, HCP details, products discussed, AI summary, sentiment, compliance status, follow-up actions, timeline
- Returns PDF as binary response with `Content-Disposition: attachment`

Alternative: Client-side PDF with `jspdf` + `html2canvas` (simpler, no backend dependency). **I'll use client-side approach** to keep backend focused.

---

### Component 8: Notification System

#### In `backend/api/routes.py`
- On interaction log → auto-create follow-up notification if follow_up_date is set
- On app load → check for overdue follow-ups → create overdue notifications
- Notifications surfaced via `GET /api/notifications`

#### In frontend
- Header bell icon with unread count badge
- Dropdown showing recent notifications
- Click → navigate to relevant interaction/follow-up

---

### Component 9: Global Search

#### `GET /api/search?q=<query>`
- Searches across: HCPs (name, specialty, institution), Interactions (notes, AI summary), Products (brand name, therapeutic area)
- Returns categorized results: `{ hcps: [...], interactions: [...], products: [...] }`

#### In frontend — `SearchModal.jsx`
- Opens with Cmd+K / Ctrl+K shortcut
- Debounced search input
- Results grouped by category with icons
- Click result → navigate to detail page

